iques them via PVT, and iteratively refines them without external supervision. This creates a closed-loop system that simulates real-world noise and learns robust filtering and repair intrinsically. Unlike VTG, which uses zero-shot correction externally, this method embeds generalization directly into the tagging mechanism through meta-behavioral clustering (e.g., grouping "time-sensitive" domains like rideshare and food delivery). The result is not just error detection, but *intent-aware synthesis*, significantly improving both accuracy and ecological validity of synthetic dialogues.

